                    { 19951, "The Last Mission is an original story and was not adapted from the Hunter x Hunter manga. It opened at #4 on the Japanese box office chart on December 28, 2013, and overall grossed a total of $7.38 million. The Last Mission was screened in the United States in July 26, 2014 at the Japan Film Festival of San Francisco.", "1 hr 37 min", null, 1, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/anime/10/62337.jpg", 2908, "R - 17+ (violence & profanity)", 7.28m, null, 2, new DateTime(2013, 12, 26, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 1, "Nen: the hidden source of energy and potential that runs through everyone, and gives those that master it a source of great power. Inside Nen is the potential for limitless light and limitless darkness. The Hunter Association has arisen to control access to it. Hunters come in many shapes and forms, and with many different appetites - but all of them have learned to master Nen, and use it to chase wealth, power, and their dreams.\n\nThe greatest and most powerful Hunter is Isaac Netero, chairman of the Hunter Association. Decades ago he sealed away Jed, a Hunter who had mastered the use of On, the dark \"shadow\" of Nen. Now On users have reappeared at the Heaven's Arena \"Battle Olympia\" tournament. For Netero, this is the last mission: to protect the Association and the world from a threat driven by hatred and the thirst for revenge. And he's going to need all the help he can get in order to succeed.", "Hunter x Hunter Movie 2: The Last Mission", "Hunter x Hunter: The Last Mission", "劇場版 HUNTERxHUNTER THE LAST MISSION", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HUUHxCSqcvU", 2, "https://myanimelist.net/anime/19951/Hunter_x_Hunter_Movie_2__The_Last_Mission" },
