                    { 30641, "", "7 min", null, 1, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/anime/2/73639.jpg", 4345, "PG-13 - Teens 13 or older", 7m, null, 2, new DateTime(2015, 8, 25, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 1, "The official website for the Yamada-kun and the Seven Witches television anime series revealed on Sunday that the anime's first Blu-ray Disc and DVD box sets will include a Yankee-kun to Megane-chan collaborative manga and anime. \n\n(Source: ANN)", "Yankee-kun na Yamada-kun to Megane-chan to Majo", null, "ヤンキー君な山田くんとメガネちゃんと魔女", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kPDIRQNciVo", 4, "https://myanimelist.net/anime/30641/Yankee-kun_na_Yamada-kun_to_Megane-chan_to_Majo" },
                    { 30654, "", "23 min per ep", new DateTime(2016, 6, 30, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 25, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/anime/8/77966.jpg", 149, "PG-13 - Teens 13 or older", 8.48m, 4, 2, new DateTime(2016, 1, 7, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 1, "Returning from their summer vacation, the students of Class 3-E at the prestigious Kunugigaoka Middle School find themselves up against unbeatable odds. Faced with the possibility of world annihilation, the students must come up with increasingly elaborate and creative ways to kill their teacher, the cunning yet optimistic and helpful Koro-sensei.\n \nHowever, eliminating Koro-sensei is not the only objective the students need to worry about. Gakuhou Asano, the academy's merciless and cruel principal, seeks to prevent Class 3-E's success by brainwashing his other hard-working pupils into ruthlessly competitive studying machines. Hostility begins to linger in the air as traitors and killers alike attempt to claim the bounty on Koro-sensei's head for themselves.\n \nNagisa Shiota, one of Class 3-E's most skilled assassins, finds himself in the middle of the conflict. While he works to maintain his academic standing and prevent the end of the world, domestic affairs jeopardize his place in Class 3-E. Together with his dedicated classmates, he must now face the threats head-on.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Ansatsu Kyoushitsu 2nd Season", "Assassination Classroom Second Season", "暗殺教室　第２期", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tZiHgr0kd7E", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/anime/30654/Ansatsu_Kyoushitsu_2nd_Season" },
                    { 30694, "Dragon Ball Super's first 27 episodes are adaptations of the films Dragon Ball Z Movie 14: Kami to Kami (episodes 1-14) and Dragon Ball Z Movie 15: Fukkatsu no F (episodes 15-27).", "23 min per ep", new DateTime(2018, 3, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 131, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/anime/7/74606.jpg", 2122, "PG-13 - Teens 13 or older", 7.45m, 2, 2, new DateTime(2015, 7, 4, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 1, "Seven years after the defeat of Majin Buu, Earth is at peace, and its people live free from any dangers lurking in the universe. However, this peace is short-lived; a sleeping threat awakens in the dark reaches of the galaxy: Beerus, the ruthless God of Destruction.\n\nDisturbed by a prophecy that he will be defeated by a \"Super Saiyan God,\" Beerus and his angelic attendant Whis search the universe for this mysterious being. Before long, they reach Earth and encounter Gokuu Son, one of the planet's mightiest warriors, and his powerful friends.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Dragon Ball Super", "Dragon Ball Super", "ドラゴンボール超（スーパー）", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nZKs2Sbx4iM", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/anime/30694/Dragon_Ball_Super" },
                    { 30704, "", "3 min per ep", new DateTime(2012, 3, 22, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 14, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/anime/4/73741.jpg", 12247, "PG-13 - Teens 13 or older", 5.4m, null, 2, new DateTime(2011, 12, 15, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 1, "Specials included in Kakko Kawaii Sengen! DVDs.", "Kakko Kawaii Sengen! Specials", null, "カッコカワイイ宣言！", null, 4, "https://myanimelist.net/anime/30704/Kakko_Kawaii_Sengen_Specials" },
                    { 30709, "", "30 min per ep", new DateTime(2016, 8, 18, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 4, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/anime/3/81250.jpg", 196, "PG-13 - Teens 13 or older", 8.4m, null, 2, new DateTime(2015, 8, 19, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 1, "While playing in the snow one day at her shrine, the land god Nanami Momozono witnesses her familiar—the fox youkai Tomoe—collapse, with dark markings appearing on his body. Tomoe's former master, Lord Mikage, appears after his long absence and places Tomoe into a magical pocket mirror in order to stave off his ailment.\n\nMikage explains that long ago, before he and Tomoe had met, the fox youkai was in love with a human woman. Seeking to live as a human with his beloved, he made a deal with a fallen god, but he only ended up cursed and dying. When Mikage discovered Tomoe, the god made the youkai forget his human love as a quick solution. However, something has changed recently to reactivate the curse; Tomoe has fallen in love with his new human master, Nanami. Since there is no way to stop the curse, Nanami wants to stop Tomoe from getting cursed in the first place by traveling back through time, even if it means they may never meet. As Nanami travels back hundreds of years to save her precious familiar, she discovers that she is far more closely bonded to Tomoe than she previously thought.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Kamisama Hajimemashita: Kako-hen", null, "神様はじめました～過去編～", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CCUSzssxM9g", 3, "https://myanimelist.net/anime/30709/Kamisama_Hajimemashita__Kako-hen" },
                    { 30727, "", "22 min per ep", new DateTime(2017, 6, 22, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 11, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/anime/2/84797.jpg", 1108, "PG-13 - Teens 13 or older", 7.76m, 1, 3, new DateTime(2017, 4, 13, 17, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 1, "After finally completing the first route of his visual novel, Blessing Software's producer Tomoya Aki is optimistic about the future of his team and achieving their goal of creating the best game of the season.\n\nHowever, they still have a long way to go. For one, Megumi Katou still has an incredibly flat personality and is unable to fit the role of Tomoya's ideal heroine. The other members of Blessing Software, Eriri Spencer Sawamura, Utaha Kasumigaoka, and Michiru Hyoudou, often forget she is even there due to her lack of presence and character. \n\nThroughout the development of their game, Blessing Software learns the struggles of working in an industry where deadlines must be met and edits are made constantly, and the hardships of working in a group setting.\n\n[Written by MAL Rewrite]", "Saenai Heroine no Sodatekata ♭", "Saekano: How to Raise a Boring Girlfriend .flat", "冴えない彼女〈ヒロイン〉の育てかた♭", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JCcvmRduwiE", 1, "https://myanimelist.net/anime/30727/Saenai_Heroine_no_Sodatekata_♭" },
                    { 30752, "", "5 min per ep", new DateTime(2013, 2, 5, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 2, "https://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/anime/2/74059.jpg", 18135, "PG-13 - Teens 13 or older", null, null, 8, new DateTime(2012, 12, 11, 16, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local), 1, "The episodes parody the Batman Begins and The Dark Knight Rises films. They were only released on the DVD/BD Box sets of himitsukesshatakanotsume.jp.", "himitsukesshatakanotsume.jp Specials", null, "秘密結社鷹の爪.jp 番外編", null, 4, "https://myanimelist.net/anime/30752/himitsukesshatakanotsumejp_Specials" },
